1
00:00:01,262 --> 00:00:03,394
[BELL RINGING]
BOYD:
Previously on
From...

2
00:00:04,439 --> 00:00:07,833
All you fucking do
is knock on our doors,

3
00:00:07,920 --> 00:00:09,966
knock on our fucking windows!

4
00:00:10,706 --> 00:00:12,925
You wanna play games?
Come get me!

5
00:00:13,013 --> 00:00:14,231
[GROANS]

6
00:00:14,318 --> 00:00:15,450
[GRUNTS]

7
00:00:15,537 --> 00:00:18,888
My blood is your blood now,
motherfucker.

8
00:00:18,975 --> 00:00:20,716
[SCREECHING]

9
00:00:20,803 --> 00:00:23,153
You really did it,
you killed one of them.

10
00:00:27,070 --> 00:00:28,245
TABITHA:
All this time,

11
00:00:28,550 --> 00:00:30,030
I thought the children
were trying to scare me, but...

12
00:00:30,117 --> 00:00:31,553
what if they're just
asking for my help?

13
00:00:31,640 --> 00:00:34,077
Though Victor said his mother
wanted to rescue the children

14
00:00:34,164 --> 00:00:35,252
locked in the tower.

15
00:00:35,339 --> 00:00:37,211
I'm sorry.
This is the only way.

16
00:00:37,298 --> 00:00:38,864
[SCREAMING]

17
00:00:40,301 --> 00:00:41,911
Are you deaf?
I said, get the--

18
00:00:42,607 --> 00:00:43,826
Where did you get that?

19
00:00:43,913 --> 00:00:45,871
You're Victor's father.

20
00:00:45,958 --> 00:00:48,613
HENRY:
My wife, Miranda,
started seeing things.

21
00:00:48,700 --> 00:00:50,398
She said it was like

22
00:00:50,485 --> 00:00:53,792
she'd been chosen
to free the children.

23
00:00:55,620 --> 00:00:57,492
[SCREAMING]
[HORN HONKS]

24
00:00:58,275 --> 00:01:00,103
But there's a town up ahead!

25
00:01:00,190 --> 00:01:01,757
You just need to keep
going forward! Please!

26
00:01:03,541 --> 00:01:05,108
[SCREECHES]
[GRUNTS]

27
00:01:08,198 --> 00:01:09,243
Victor.

28
00:01:09,330 --> 00:01:11,810
I didn't know
how to get home.

29
00:01:11,897 --> 00:01:13,508
[VICTOR CRIES]

30
00:01:13,986 --> 00:01:16,032
The Boy in White was
trying to tell Christopher

31
00:01:16,119 --> 00:01:17,338
that to save the children,

32
00:01:17,425 --> 00:01:19,601
he would have to
go through the tree.

33
00:01:19,688 --> 00:01:21,951
Christopher wouldn't
go in the tree,

34
00:01:22,038 --> 00:01:24,562
so I told my mother
what the Boy in White said.

35
00:01:24,649 --> 00:01:26,129
It was my fault.

36
00:01:26,216 --> 00:01:27,913
I was the reason
that she died.

37
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,394
She was trying
to protect you.

38
00:01:30,481 --> 00:01:32,222
That's my job now.

39
00:01:32,309 --> 00:01:33,571
We thought you were dead.

40
00:01:34,268 --> 00:01:36,531
Your children
thought you were dead.

41
00:01:36,618 --> 00:01:38,533
You owe it to your kids
to be here now.

42
00:01:39,273 --> 00:01:41,579
This place
wants us to be scared.

43
00:01:41,666 --> 00:01:44,800
How we take care of each other,
and how we always do our best,

44
00:01:44,887 --> 00:01:46,671
that's what matters.

45
00:01:46,758 --> 00:01:47,846
You're not pregnant.

46
00:01:47,933 --> 00:01:49,109
I am pregnant!

47
00:01:49,196 --> 00:01:50,588
I can feel it!

48
00:01:50,675 --> 00:01:53,635
I'm not eating garbage
because I'm afraid!

49
00:01:53,722 --> 00:01:55,376
It's making me!

50
00:01:55,463 --> 00:01:58,292
Whatever is inside me,
it's getting stronger.

51
00:01:58,379 --> 00:02:01,512
Help me, Elgin.
I can save all of you.

52
00:02:01,599 --> 00:02:03,601
I can help you go back home.

53
00:02:03,688 --> 00:02:05,516
FATIMA: Elgin, please!

54
00:02:05,603 --> 00:02:08,911
Fatima's baby
is going to save all of us.

55
00:02:08,998 --> 00:02:10,478
He's not gonna
tell you where she is.

56
00:02:10,565 --> 00:02:13,524
You said that you weren't
gonna let this place break you.

57
00:02:15,178 --> 00:02:16,484
This place has won.

58
00:02:16,571 --> 00:02:19,008
[GRUNTS]
[SCREAMING]

59
00:02:19,922 --> 00:02:21,228
What the fuck are you doing?

60
00:02:21,315 --> 00:02:25,188
Boyd doesn't understand
how far he needs to go.

61
00:02:25,275 --> 00:02:26,233
Sara--

62
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:27,669
She's in the root cellar.

63
00:02:27,843 --> 00:02:30,541
BOYD:
I'm not gonna be
blindsided by this place again.

64
00:02:30,628 --> 00:02:31,890
I need to see it.

65
00:02:32,630 --> 00:02:34,676
FATIMA:
Those things
that come out at night,

66
00:02:34,763 --> 00:02:37,157
they sacrificed their children,

67
00:02:37,244 --> 00:02:40,508
because it promised them
that they would live forever.

68
00:02:46,253 --> 00:02:48,298
JADE: Miranda had
visions of this place.

69
00:02:48,385 --> 00:02:50,344
She's the only one who had
a connection to this place

70
00:02:50,431 --> 00:02:51,475
long before she arrived.

71
00:02:51,562 --> 00:02:52,911
It wasn't just Miranda.

72
00:02:52,998 --> 00:02:56,828
When I was a little girl,
I saw this place, too.

73
00:02:56,915 --> 00:03:01,529
[VIOLIN PLAYING MOURNFUL TUNE]

74
00:03:01,616 --> 00:03:02,791
Anghkooey.

75
00:03:02,878 --> 00:03:04,314
Remember.

76
00:03:04,401 --> 00:03:05,924
Oh, God.

77
00:03:06,011 --> 00:03:09,450
TABITHA:
The reason
I felt what Miranda felt

78
00:03:09,537 --> 00:03:11,016
is because I was Miranda.

79
00:03:11,103 --> 00:03:13,758
And Jade was Christopher.
We've come back

80
00:03:13,845 --> 00:03:16,935
over and over again because
we failed the first time.

81
00:03:17,022 --> 00:03:18,546
I need some time, honey.

82
00:03:20,809 --> 00:03:22,767
JULIE:
When I walked
inside the ruins,

83
00:03:22,854 --> 00:03:24,769
suddenly,
I was in a chamber.

84
00:03:24,856 --> 00:03:25,857
[SCREAMING]

85
00:03:25,944 --> 00:03:27,337
I think I was actually there.

86
00:03:27,424 --> 00:03:29,948
You're a Storywalker:
someone who can visit

87
00:03:30,035 --> 00:03:32,124
chapters of the story
that already happened.

88
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:33,213
What?

89
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:34,736
But you can't change them.

90
00:03:34,823 --> 00:03:36,825
Dad! I think
this is when it happens!

91
00:03:36,912 --> 00:03:38,261
Slow down.
No, no, listen to me!

92
00:03:38,348 --> 00:03:40,524
I need to change
the story, Dad, please!

93
00:03:40,611 --> 00:03:42,831
That was a hell of a song.

94
00:03:42,918 --> 00:03:45,050
This didn't have
to happen, you know.

95
00:03:45,137 --> 00:03:47,183
Knowledge comes with a cost.

96
00:03:47,618 --> 00:03:49,272
[CHOKING]

97
00:03:49,359 --> 00:03:51,579
Your wife shouldn't
have dug that hole, Jim.

98
00:03:51,666 --> 00:03:52,971
[CHOKING]

99
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:57,846
No!

100
00:04:00,065 --> 00:04:02,242
[SCREAMING]

101
00:04:03,460 --> 00:04:06,507
[SIGHS] People are
such fragile things.

102
00:04:07,464 --> 00:04:09,466
We have to stop
meeting like this.

103
00:04:10,989 --> 00:04:12,643
When did you
come from this time?

104
00:04:12,730 --> 00:04:14,079
[GASPING]

105
00:04:14,166 --> 00:04:15,820
Didn't anyone tell ya?

106
00:04:16,473 --> 00:04:19,520
There's no way to change
a story once it's been told.

107
00:04:22,174 --> 00:04:23,654
[SIGHS]

108
00:04:30,139 --> 00:04:31,445
Just you and me now, Jim.

109
00:04:33,273 --> 00:04:37,625
I liked you,
I really did.

110
00:04:37,712 --> 00:04:39,366
[WHISPERS] Fuck you.

111
00:04:39,453 --> 00:04:43,021
[CHUCKLES]
You always tried so hard.

112
00:04:44,327 --> 00:04:45,894
You carried so much.

113
00:04:48,157 --> 00:04:51,421
It's a terrible shame you won't
get to see what happens next.

114
00:04:53,249 --> 00:04:54,946
Because what happens next...

115
00:04:56,383 --> 00:04:58,298
is my favorite part.

116
00:05:00,169 --> 00:05:01,823
Would you like to know why?

117
00:05:02,954 --> 00:05:05,479
[CHUCKLES]

118
00:05:21,625 --> 00:05:22,757
[SIGHS]

119
00:05:32,723 --> 00:05:37,511
["QUE SERA, SERA [WHATEVER
WILL BE, WILL BE]" PLAYS]

120
00:05:42,646 --> 00:05:47,477
♪
When I was just a little boy
♪

121
00:05:47,564 --> 00:05:49,914
♪
I asked my father
♪

122
00:05:50,001 --> 00:05:52,352
♪
"What will I be?"
♪

123
00:05:53,701 --> 00:05:56,051
♪
"Will I be handsome?"
♪

124
00:05:56,138 --> 00:05:58,488
♪
"Will I be rich?"
♪

125
00:05:58,575 --> 00:06:01,709
♪
Here's what he said to me
♪

126
00:06:02,623 --> 00:06:05,539
♪
Que sera sera
♪

127
00:06:06,801 --> 00:06:10,195
♪
Whatever will be will be
♪

128
00:06:11,675 --> 00:06:15,026
♪
The future's not ours to see
♪

129
00:06:15,853 --> 00:06:18,639
♪
Que sera sera
♪

130
00:06:20,858 --> 00:06:23,818
♪
What will be will be ♪

131
00:06:33,175 --> 00:06:38,049
♪
Now I have
children of my own
♪

132
00:06:38,136 --> 00:06:40,443
♪
They ask their father
♪

133
00:06:40,530 --> 00:06:42,837
♪
"What will I be?"
♪

134
00:06:44,186 --> 00:06:46,667
♪
"Will I be pretty?"
♪

135
00:06:46,754 --> 00:06:49,104
♪
"Will I be rich?"
♪

136
00:06:49,191 --> 00:06:52,281
♪
I tell them tenderly
♪

137
00:06:53,151 --> 00:06:55,806
♪
Que sera sera
♪

138
00:06:57,286 --> 00:07:00,681
♪
Whatever will be will be
♪

139
00:07:02,334 --> 00:07:06,208
♪
The future's not ours to see
♪

140
00:07:06,295 --> 00:07:09,385
♪
Que sera sera
♪

141
00:07:11,387 --> 00:07:14,390
♪
What will be will be
♪

142
00:07:16,610 --> 00:07:19,482
♪
Que sera sera
♪

143
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:36,586
What do you mean, they
sacrificed their children?

144
00:07:36,673 --> 00:07:38,327
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

145
00:07:38,414 --> 00:07:42,113
Those things in the woods;
they were people once.

146
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:44,768
They made a--

147
00:07:45,900 --> 00:07:50,295
a bargain with
something horrible.

148
00:07:50,382 --> 00:07:52,428
But I didn't see--

149
00:07:52,515 --> 00:07:54,125
I-I couldn't see it. I--

150
00:07:54,952 --> 00:07:56,780
ELLIS: It's okay.
It's okay. Hey.

151
00:07:57,520 --> 00:07:58,521
[SCREAMS]

152
00:07:58,695 --> 00:08:00,262
Hey, hey, hey.
You're okay. You're okay.

153
00:08:00,349 --> 00:08:01,568
We gotta get her out of here.

154
00:08:01,655 --> 00:08:02,873
Baby, we gotta go,
all right?

155
00:08:02,960 --> 00:08:04,484
No. Boyd was here.
Where's Boyd?

156
00:08:04,571 --> 00:08:07,225
I'll find him. Go! Come on.
We can't leave without him.

157
00:08:07,312 --> 00:08:08,792
Fatima, we have to go!
Come on.

158
00:08:08,879 --> 00:08:10,141
Ellis!
Please.

159
00:08:10,228 --> 00:08:11,447
No. I'm okay, I can--
Hey.

160
00:08:11,534 --> 00:08:14,058
[SHOUTS IN PAIN]
Hey! Help me. Hey! Hey!

161
00:08:14,145 --> 00:08:16,713
[SHOUTS IN PAIN]
I know, I know.

162
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:19,499
Hey, you're okay.
Come on. Kenny.

163
00:08:19,586 --> 00:08:21,152
But, we can't--

164
00:08:21,805 --> 00:08:24,155
He's gonna be okay.
He's gonna be okay.

165
00:08:24,242 --> 00:08:25,983
Come on, baby.
All right?

166
00:08:26,070 --> 00:08:28,333
We gotta go.
We gotta go.

167
00:08:28,420 --> 00:08:30,727
We're gonna be okay.
Come on.

168
00:08:30,814 --> 00:08:33,382
It's okay.
Come on. I got you.

169
00:08:33,469 --> 00:08:36,559
[FATIMA BREATHING SHAKILY]

170
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:39,431
ELLIS: I got you.

171
00:08:41,912 --> 00:08:42,957
You good?

172
00:08:43,044 --> 00:08:45,350
Yeah.
Okay, come on. Let's go.

173
00:08:46,003 --> 00:08:48,484
[WOOD CREAKING]

174
00:09:06,241 --> 00:09:07,416
Boyd?

175
00:09:28,568 --> 00:09:29,569
Boyd!

176
00:09:41,972 --> 00:09:43,191
[WHISPERS] Boyd?

177
00:10:04,473 --> 00:10:08,651
Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.

178
00:10:08,738 --> 00:10:11,132
Hey. Hey. Shh.

179
00:10:11,219 --> 00:10:13,308
We gotta get outta here.
Okay?

180
00:10:13,395 --> 00:10:14,570
Okay.

181
00:10:14,657 --> 00:10:16,093
We gotta go that way.

182
00:10:18,356 --> 00:10:19,619
Hello, Kenny.

183
00:10:21,795 --> 00:10:23,927
It's nice to see you again.

184
00:10:24,014 --> 00:10:25,755
No.Move, move!

185
00:10:25,842 --> 00:10:27,583
Now! Move! Go, go!

186
00:10:29,498 --> 00:10:31,326
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

187
00:10:31,413 --> 00:10:32,980
Keep going!
Keep going! Move it!

188
00:10:33,807 --> 00:10:35,591
We got it! Keep going!

189
00:10:35,678 --> 00:10:38,333
Come on!
Hurry up.

190
00:10:39,464 --> 00:10:42,119
Watch out!
What the fuck?!

191
00:10:42,206 --> 00:10:44,034
How?! He didn't--

192
00:10:44,121 --> 00:10:45,732
I know.
We-- We burned him!

193
00:10:45,819 --> 00:10:47,690
We fucking burned him!
I know! I know!

194
00:10:48,778 --> 00:10:50,780
My God. How did--
how did he even get--

195
00:10:50,867 --> 00:10:52,042
The baby.

196
00:10:52,956 --> 00:10:54,001
What?

197
00:10:54,088 --> 00:10:55,350
The baby.

198
00:10:56,786 --> 00:10:58,440
I watched it grow.

199
00:10:58,527 --> 00:11:00,660
'Kay?
I watched it stand up...

200
00:11:00,747 --> 00:11:02,270
and smile.

201
00:11:04,794 --> 00:11:06,187
You're--

202
00:11:06,317 --> 00:11:09,190
You're telling me that Fatima
gave birth to that thing?

203
00:11:09,277 --> 00:11:10,582
Is that what you're saying?

204
00:11:12,976 --> 00:11:14,021
Yeah.

205
00:11:17,764 --> 00:11:18,721
You good?

206
00:11:18,808 --> 00:11:20,331
Yeah, I'm fine.
Can you just--

207
00:11:20,418 --> 00:11:21,942
can you just please
tell me what's going on?

208
00:11:22,029 --> 00:11:23,378
I will.
Donna!

209
00:11:28,122 --> 00:11:29,689
Any word from Boyd yet?

210
00:11:30,777 --> 00:11:32,953
[VOICES CHATTERING]

211
00:11:34,171 --> 00:11:35,912
People are starting
to come back.

212
00:11:35,999 --> 00:11:37,914
[FOOTSTEPS THUDDING]

213
00:11:38,001 --> 00:11:39,046
I should go.

214
00:11:39,133 --> 00:11:40,090
Yeah.

215
00:11:41,831 --> 00:11:42,832
That's probably best.

216
00:11:49,752 --> 00:11:51,493
Donna, what the fuck
is going on?

217
00:11:51,580 --> 00:11:52,624
In here.

218
00:11:55,018 --> 00:11:56,890
[WHIMPERING]

219
00:11:58,848 --> 00:11:59,893
[DOOR OPENS]

220
00:12:00,545 --> 00:12:01,851
Jesus.

221
00:12:01,938 --> 00:12:04,593
Hey. Put that down.

222
00:12:04,680 --> 00:12:06,377
She's here to help.

223
00:12:06,464 --> 00:12:08,031
Oh, come--
for fuck's sake,

224
00:12:08,118 --> 00:12:10,599
we all know it's not loaded!
Just put it away.

225
00:12:13,907 --> 00:12:16,518
Now go. You got
nothing else to do here.

226
00:12:22,611 --> 00:12:24,439
Fine. Then stay.

227
00:12:26,789 --> 00:12:28,530
[SIGHS]
Elgin.

228
00:12:29,531 --> 00:12:30,575
Elgin?

229
00:12:30,662 --> 00:12:32,752
Kristi's here to help you.

230
00:12:32,839 --> 00:12:33,970
Can you hear me?

231
00:12:34,057 --> 00:12:36,668
I need you
to roll over. Okay?

232
00:12:36,756 --> 00:12:39,193
Come on. Come on.

233
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:41,369
Just careful. Okay.
There. Come on.

234
00:12:42,326 --> 00:12:44,372
Okay, now's the part where
you tell me what happened.

235
00:12:45,025 --> 00:12:47,288
Sara took his eye out
with a screwdriver.

236
00:12:49,029 --> 00:12:50,770
She had reasons.

237
00:12:50,857 --> 00:12:52,423
Can you get me a chair?
Yeah.

238
00:12:52,510 --> 00:12:53,598
Okay.

239
00:12:55,296 --> 00:12:56,297
Okay.

240
00:12:57,167 --> 00:12:58,212
Thank you.

241
00:12:59,430 --> 00:13:00,780
Okay, Elgin,

242
00:13:01,737 --> 00:13:02,782
can you take
your hand away?

243
00:13:03,521 --> 00:13:04,609
It's okay.

244
00:13:08,352 --> 00:13:09,397
[EXHALES]

245
00:13:09,484 --> 00:13:11,312
DONNA:
Can you stitch him up?

246
00:13:13,488 --> 00:13:14,837
Yeah, I can do my best.

247
00:13:15,664 --> 00:13:16,839
Donna, why--

248
00:13:16,926 --> 00:13:18,449
Let's talk later.
[CLARA] Donna?

249
00:13:18,536 --> 00:13:19,450
Yes! Just hold on, Clara!

250
00:13:19,537 --> 00:13:20,582
Fatima's back.

251
00:13:20,712 --> 00:13:22,105
She and Ellis
are coming up the hill.

252
00:13:22,192 --> 00:13:23,324
Okay, okay.
What happened?

253
00:13:23,411 --> 00:13:25,152
No, nothing! Nothing!
Back out!

254
00:13:25,239 --> 00:13:27,241
Can I get some ice?
Yeah. Go!

255
00:13:42,125 --> 00:13:44,214
[EXHALES]

256
00:13:56,792 --> 00:13:58,533
Yeah.

257
00:14:01,231 --> 00:14:04,104
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

258
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:28,476
Boyd! What--

259
00:14:29,129 --> 00:14:30,260
What--

260
00:14:31,044 --> 00:14:33,176
Boyd, what are we doing?

261
00:14:33,263 --> 00:14:35,483
