Uh, do you have a phone? I, um--
I left mine in the car, and I--

777
00:38:39,186 --> 00:38:41,797
I-I need to call my mom.
She's probably worried sick.

778
00:38:43,059 --> 00:38:44,800
Yeah, um, there's, uh...

779
00:38:45,932 --> 00:38:49,370
There's no...
There's no cell service here.

780
00:38:49,457 --> 00:38:50,850
I could just go
down the hill. It's okay.

781
00:38:50,937 --> 00:38:52,330
I-I don't mean...

782
00:38:53,156 --> 00:38:55,681
I don't mean
here in the clinic.

783
00:38:55,768 --> 00:38:57,030
MARIELLE:
I'm gonna go.

784
00:38:58,727 --> 00:39:00,207
I, uh...

785
00:39:00,294 --> 00:39:01,382
What's going on?

786
00:39:02,644 --> 00:39:04,690
I-I need to call my mom.

787
00:39:04,777 --> 00:39:07,214
I know. I understand, I do.

788
00:39:08,215 --> 00:39:11,653
I...
I wish I could, um...

789
00:39:13,655 --> 00:39:18,094
We need to have a talk...
about this place,

790
00:39:19,139 --> 00:39:21,359
and about that tree
that you saw in the road.

791
00:39:30,280 --> 00:39:31,586
JULIE: Mom.

792
00:39:32,892 --> 00:39:34,023
Where is he?

793
00:39:34,894 --> 00:39:36,635
Why isn't he back yet?

794
00:39:36,722 --> 00:39:38,637
Honey,
your father's fine.

795
00:39:38,724 --> 00:39:41,117
It's not like he's late
coming home from work.

796
00:39:41,204 --> 00:39:44,425
Mom, what happened today?
Why won't you talk to me?

797
00:39:44,512 --> 00:39:46,514
No, Julie, no.
I-I don't wanna talk right now.

798
00:39:46,601 --> 00:39:47,863
Please!
I can't.

799
00:39:47,950 --> 00:39:48,951
Please!
I can't talk to you.

800
00:39:49,343 --> 00:39:50,866
I can't talk to you now.
Stop saying that! Please!

801
00:39:50,953 --> 00:39:54,087
Mom, It's almost dark.
He's not home.

802
00:39:54,174 --> 00:39:55,349
Please, why won't you talk--

803
00:39:55,436 --> 00:39:57,960
ETHAN: Stop it.
Stop yelling at each other.

804
00:39:59,701 --> 00:40:02,748
No, I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

805
00:40:03,923 --> 00:40:05,794
[DOOR CLOSES]
Is Dad dead?

806
00:40:07,100 --> 00:40:08,231
No!

807
00:40:09,232 --> 00:40:10,886
No, honey. No, he's not.

808
00:40:12,845 --> 00:40:15,630
[SIGHS] Maybe he didn't
realize how late it was.

809
00:40:16,370 --> 00:40:17,327
I don't know.

810
00:40:17,632 --> 00:40:21,288
Maybe he's at
the Colony House or the RV.

811
00:40:22,507 --> 00:40:23,943
We'll see him tomorrow.

812
00:40:24,683 --> 00:40:26,119
Well, what if we don't?

813
00:40:27,860 --> 00:40:28,904
Well...

814
00:40:28,991 --> 00:40:30,558
Do you remember
what Dad said to us,

815
00:40:30,645 --> 00:40:32,299
the night that Mom
went to the Bottle Tree

816
00:40:32,386 --> 00:40:33,822
and didn't come home?

817
00:40:34,780 --> 00:40:37,304
He said all we have in this
place is what we believe.

818
00:40:37,391 --> 00:40:39,480
So, we have to
believe good things.

819
00:40:40,525 --> 00:40:41,656
Right?

820
00:40:42,875 --> 00:40:44,267
Mom came home.

821
00:40:46,182 --> 00:40:47,575
Dad will, too.

822
00:40:53,146 --> 00:40:58,281
So, um, the monsters, they--
they come every night?

823
00:40:58,368 --> 00:40:59,544
Yeah.

824
00:40:59,631 --> 00:41:02,677
These-- These rocks,
they-- they protect you?

825
00:41:03,504 --> 00:41:05,811
Uh, we call them talismans.

826
00:41:05,898 --> 00:41:09,336
How do they work?
Don't! Don't, um...

827
00:41:10,337 --> 00:41:11,991
Don't take it off the window.

828
00:41:12,078 --> 00:41:13,383
Sorry.

829
00:41:13,471 --> 00:41:14,994
It's okay.
It's just, um...

830
00:41:15,777 --> 00:41:17,692
they have to be
hanging for it to work.

831
00:41:18,519 --> 00:41:19,607
Why?

832
00:41:22,131 --> 00:41:23,698
[EXHALES] Uh...

833
00:41:24,394 --> 00:41:25,831
We-- We don't know.

834
00:41:27,006 --> 00:41:28,573
We don't know.

835
00:41:28,660 --> 00:41:30,879
I know how
this must all sound.

836
00:41:30,966 --> 00:41:32,577
"The light shines
in the darkness,

837
00:41:32,664 --> 00:41:34,361
and the darkness
shall not overcome it."

838
00:41:34,448 --> 00:41:35,884
What is that?

839
00:41:35,971 --> 00:41:37,451
John 1:5.

840
00:41:37,538 --> 00:41:39,845
It means that,
um, God is with us,

841
00:41:39,932 --> 00:41:41,020
even here.

842
00:41:41,760 --> 00:41:45,633
I mean, um, how else can you
explain such a magical thing

843
00:41:45,720 --> 00:41:47,374
to keep the darkness at bay?

844
00:41:49,158 --> 00:41:50,203
Right.

845
00:41:50,290 --> 00:41:52,292
Will you pray
with me, Kenny?

846
00:41:53,815 --> 00:41:55,034
Oh, I'm not--

847
00:41:55,643 --> 00:41:56,992
I'm not really, uh...

848
00:41:57,602 --> 00:41:58,777
I'm not really religious.

849
00:41:58,864 --> 00:42:01,257
That's okay.
God still listens.

850
00:42:03,042 --> 00:42:04,173
Please?

851
00:42:06,567 --> 00:42:08,438
Yeah. Yeah, sure.

852
00:42:12,921 --> 00:42:13,922
[EXHALES]

853
00:42:15,315 --> 00:42:18,274
Lord, please protect us
in this dark place,

854
00:42:18,361 --> 00:42:20,276
where evil roams so freely.

855
00:42:21,234 --> 00:42:23,062
Please stand by
my daddy's bedside

856
00:42:23,149 --> 00:42:25,412
and let him wake
renewed in your love.

857
00:42:25,499 --> 00:42:28,371
And please rest your hand upon
the shoulders of these people,

858
00:42:28,458 --> 00:42:30,373
trapped here in this place,
who have taken us in

859
00:42:30,460 --> 00:42:32,071
and shown us such kindness.

860
00:42:32,854 --> 00:42:34,334
Be with them tonight,
O Lord,

861
00:42:34,421 --> 00:42:36,597
and let your love
give them rest.

862
00:42:36,684 --> 00:42:39,774
This we ask in your name.
Amen.

863
00:42:42,821 --> 00:42:44,039
Uh, Amen.

864
00:42:46,172 --> 00:42:49,088
Um, I'm gonna go sit with
my daddy now, if that's okay.

865
00:42:49,175 --> 00:42:50,872
Yeah. Of course.

866
00:43:35,003 --> 00:43:36,701
There are a lot of people
wanting to know

867
00:43:36,788 --> 00:43:38,180
what happened down there.

868
00:43:40,400 --> 00:43:43,403
Boyd? You hear what I said?

869
00:43:44,230 --> 00:43:45,666
We had another car today.

870
00:43:47,102 --> 00:43:48,582
A girl and her dad.

871
00:43:49,801 --> 00:43:53,152
Looked like a...
like a pastor, maybe.

872
00:43:55,197 --> 00:43:57,504
He had a--
he had a stroke...

873
00:43:58,897 --> 00:44:01,551
or a seizure or something.

874
00:44:01,639 --> 00:44:04,772
They crashed into
the Sheriff's Station.

875
00:44:06,208 --> 00:44:08,341
The girl can't be more than,
I don't know, 15,

876
00:44:09,342 --> 00:44:11,344
16 years old. She's, uh...

877
00:44:11,431 --> 00:44:13,607
She's up at
the clinic right now,

878
00:44:13,694 --> 00:44:15,522
waiting to see if her dad
lives through the night,

879
00:44:15,609 --> 00:44:17,045
while Kenny explains to her

880
00:44:17,132 --> 00:44:19,787
that whatever life
she had before...

881
00:44:21,223 --> 00:44:22,529
is over,

882
00:44:22,616 --> 00:44:24,879
that, now,
she lives in a place

883
00:44:24,966 --> 00:44:27,012
where monsters smile.

884
00:44:30,711 --> 00:44:32,452
That girl's probably
gonna die here.

885
00:44:32,539 --> 00:44:34,149
Boyd!
BOYD: You know,

886
00:44:34,976 --> 00:44:38,458
the only thing that gets me
out of bed in the morning

887
00:44:38,545 --> 00:44:39,981
is the idea that...

888
00:44:41,243 --> 00:44:44,638
maybe, just-- just maybe,
we can beat this place,

889
00:44:45,726 --> 00:44:48,424
that maybe we can
get everybody home,

890
00:44:48,511 --> 00:44:50,644
that, someday, maybe

891
00:44:50,731 --> 00:44:53,952
the good guys actually win!

892
00:44:55,040 --> 00:44:57,607
And then, I saw that
fucking thing in the tunnels!

893
00:44:58,391 --> 00:45:01,611
The same goddamn smile.
That same...

894
00:45:01,699 --> 00:45:03,439
And I realized--

895
00:45:03,526 --> 00:45:06,138
I mean, this place has been
three steps ahead of us

896
00:45:06,225 --> 00:45:07,487
from the beginning!

897
00:45:07,574 --> 00:45:09,924
Just like you said:
the game's rigged.

898
00:45:10,011 --> 00:45:11,447
Doesn't matter what we do.

899
00:45:11,534 --> 00:45:13,362
Doesn't matter
what we sacrifice.

900
00:45:13,449 --> 00:45:16,583
None of it means
a goddamn thing if we can't--

901
00:45:17,889 --> 00:45:18,977
Hey, where you going?

902
00:45:19,064 --> 00:45:21,022
I am not going anywhere.

903
00:45:22,110 --> 00:45:23,285
None of us are.

904
00:45:24,286 --> 00:45:25,766
Okay, no, fuck this.

905
00:45:26,636 --> 00:45:27,681
Get out of my way, Kristi!

906
00:45:27,768 --> 00:45:30,031
No, no.
You don't get to do this.

907
00:45:30,118 --> 00:45:31,685
It's a pretty shit time
for you to start

908
00:45:31,772 --> 00:45:34,035
feeling sorry for yourself.
Oh, is that what I'm doing?

909
00:45:34,122 --> 00:45:35,776
Yeah, you are!

910
00:45:35,863 --> 00:45:37,691
And you have
plenty of reasons to.

911
00:45:37,778 --> 00:45:40,607
So does everybody else here.
But none of those people

912
00:45:40,694 --> 00:45:43,436
are asking me to stitch up
people's eye sockets,

913
00:45:43,523 --> 00:45:45,394
so I'm gonna need
a little more from you

914
00:45:45,481 --> 00:45:47,005
than "These monsters
live forever,

915
00:45:47,092 --> 00:45:49,877
so we're all gonna die."
Because it doesn't matter

916
00:45:49,964 --> 00:45:52,097
how many people
I stitch back up together,

917
00:45:52,750 --> 00:45:54,926
if they see you lose faith,

918
00:45:55,013 --> 00:45:56,579
then that's when people
start hanging themselves

919
00:45:56,666 --> 00:45:57,711
in the bathroom.

920
00:45:58,712 --> 00:46:00,540
Can you guys
give us a second?

921
00:46:02,237 --> 00:46:03,412
Yeah.

922
00:46:03,499 --> 00:46:05,284
DONNA: Let's go.

923
00:46:05,371 --> 00:46:07,112
[CLEARS THROAT]

924
00:46:07,199 --> 00:46:08,330
Let's go.

925
00:46:25,957 --> 00:46:27,523
Kristi's right, Dad.

926
00:46:28,873 --> 00:46:31,353
Look, no matter what happens,

927
00:46:31,440 --> 00:46:35,401
you are the one person
that nobody here can see...

928
00:46:37,882 --> 00:46:40,101
Dad!
I can't do it anymore.

929
00:46:40,798 --> 00:46:42,060
Ellis, I can't!

930
00:46:42,974 --> 00:46:44,497
I'm falling apart!

931
00:46:47,761 --> 00:46:51,765
Everything I've done,
every sacrifice we've made,

932
00:46:52,679 --> 00:46:55,638
and if--
if I can't get you home,

933
00:46:55,725 --> 00:46:58,163
then none of it matters!
Your mom?

934
00:46:58,250 --> 00:46:59,729
Your mom?

935
00:46:59,817 --> 00:47:00,861
It's...

936
00:47:02,384 --> 00:47:04,082
Fuck, it can't be
for nothing!

937
00:47:04,169 --> 00:47:05,692
I just-- I...

938
00:47:05,779 --> 00:47:08,260
[VOICE BREAKING]
I can't fucking...

939
00:47:09,739 --> 00:47:11,306
I cannot...

940
00:47:12,525 --> 00:47:13,700
...any...

941
00:47:14,788 --> 00:47:15,876
God.

942
00:47:15,963 --> 00:47:20,228
[SOBBING]

943
00:47:20,315 --> 00:47:21,490
ELLIS: I know.

944
00:47:23,928 --> 00:47:25,016
I know.

945
00:47:25,712 --> 00:47:26,800
[SOBBING]

946
00:47:38,725 --> 00:47:40,770
[METALLIC CLATTERING]

947
00:47:42,685 --> 00:47:43,991
What was that?

948
00:47:45,427 --> 00:47:46,646
I don't know.

949
00:47:48,735 --> 00:47:49,867
Mom?

950
00:48:30,429 --> 00:48:31,386
What's happening?

951
00:49:21,654 --> 00:49:25,963
[SOPHIA BREATHING DEEPLY]

952
00:49:30,141 --> 00:49:31,229
[WHISPERING] Wake up.

953
00:49:37,452 --> 00:49:38,540
That's better.

954
00:49:40,586 --> 00:49:42,370
Blink twice
if you can hear me.

955
00:49:45,417 --> 00:49:48,115
I know this must be
very confusing for you.

956
00:49:48,202 --> 00:49:50,900
But it's important
you understand

957
00:49:50,988 --> 00:49:55,993
that you played a very special
role in a very important story.

958
00:50:06,394 --> 00:50:07,787
You see, um...

959
00:50:09,267 --> 00:50:11,225
I couldn't come
to them as I was.

960
00:50:16,056 --> 00:50:17,623
[EXHALES]

961
00:50:17,710 --> 00:50:18,754
[LAUGHS]

962
00:50:19,016 --> 00:50:21,235
SOPHIA:
Not with everything
they learned.

963
00:50:30,201 --> 00:50:33,160
[GROANING]

964
00:50:39,949 --> 00:50:41,516
[CRACKING]

965
00:50:45,172 --> 00:50:46,826
[BONES CRACKING]

966
00:50:46,913 --> 00:50:48,915
[GROANING CONTINUES]

967
00:50:49,002 --> 00:50:52,788
[CRACKING]

968
00:50:54,834 --> 00:50:57,141
[SOPHIA GROANING]

969
00:50:58,838 --> 00:51:01,580
[BONES CRACKING]

970
00:51:14,375 --> 00:51:16,986
What's happening
to you isn't fair.

971
00:51:28,650 --> 00:51:29,695
Are you all right?

972
00:51:29,782 --> 00:51:31,131
I'm lost.

973
00:51:31,218 --> 00:51:32,306
Me too.

974
00:51:34,047 --> 00:51:35,353
Would you like a ride?

975
00:51:38,617 --> 00:51:40,140
When you stopped for me,

976
00:51:40,227 --> 00:51:42,316
I know you did so
with kindness in your heart.

977
00:51:49,410 --> 00:51:50,933
[GASPING]

978
00:51:52,413 --> 00:51:54,111
[ENGINE REVVING]

979
00:51:55,677 --> 00:51:56,722
[ENGINE REVVING]

980
00:51:56,809 --> 00:51:58,332
[TIRES SCREECHING]

981
00:52:00,769 --> 00:52:02,423
You must be so afraid.

982
00:52:03,990 --> 00:52:06,688
I'm sorry you won't be here
to see what comes next.

983
00:52:07,515 --> 00:52:09,474
It's always
my favorite part.

984
00:52:12,172 --> 00:52:14,305
It's the part I wish
could last forever.

985
00:52:16,829 --> 00:52:18,439
Would you like to know why?

986
00:52:24,228 --> 00:52:26,882
This is when
they tear themselves apart.

987
00:52:29,798 --> 00:52:32,323
[MUFFLED GRUNTING]
